	</voice>
	<tense nb="a tense can  be active|passive, as well as indicative|subjunctive">pluperfect|perfect|imperfect|present|futureperfect|future
		<pluperfect>an action which occurred two stages back in the past, expressed in English with "had" plus Past Participle</pluperfect><perfect>refers mostly to single, completed actions in the past; formed with 1ps_PfIA</perfect><imperfect>imperfect means incomplete; actions in the past which didn't get finished, went on regularly, lasted for some time before they ended or only just got started; as opposed to single actions which were completed in one go; however, the normal past tense can be used if it's clear that the action took place over a period of time, eg: I wrote in my diary every day</imperfect></tense>
