			<vocative>for addressing someone directly</vocative>
			<accusative>direct object|used after certain prepositions|duration of time|motion towards|adverbial</accusative>
			<genitive>denotes posssession|wide range of other meanings|contains the noun's stem</genitive>
			<dative>indirect object (to|for)|wide range of other meanings</dative>
			<ablative>denotes means|association or separation (by|with|from)|used after certain prepositions|(by|of|with|in|from)</ablative>
			<locative>in relation to a particular place (at|towards|from)</locative>
		</case>
